These were at first, in the reign of the Tarquins„ deposited in the Capitol; but, after the destruction of the Capitol and its contents by fite in the time of Sulla, 82 B.c.‚ no new collection of such books for state purposes was made, until the building of the above-mentioned temple of Apollo.
